data.text:
Misao Senbongi (千本木 操, Senbogi Misao?) is a Japanese composer of video game music. Senbongi's first work with Capcom was as part of Masami Ueda's team that composed for BIOHAZARD 4, which became Devil May Cry. She would later work on the Resident Evil and Resident Evil 4 soundtracks, both under Shusaku Uchiyama.[1][2]
